title: Customs computers at US airports down for about 90 minutes
text:
> Top News Customs computers at US airports down for about 90 minutes In this photo provided by Ashley Hopkins, people wait in lines at Dallas-Fort Worth Airport in Dallas, Wednesday, Oct. 14, 2015. U.S. Customs and Border Protection says the computer systems used to process international travelers at airports across the United States went down for about 90 minutes Wednesday evening.
